cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the capacity of fading channels, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
2. cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the capacity of single-input single-output (SISO) and multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) channels, which are commonly used in wireless communication networks. 
3. cs.SI (Systems and Control) - The paper considers the constraints on the transmit antennas, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless communication channels, which are a key component of networking and internet architecture. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper discusses the capacity of MIMO channels, which can be seen as a multiagent system where each antenna is an agent.
